cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with reconstructing 3D models from 2D images. Additionally, the use of deep learning and adversarial networks suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The generation of 3D volumetric objects also suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of synthesized images may suggest that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
